From 439db2b3ec30a5d02106d3bcc738197810d76fe8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 24 Jun 2026 15:16:32 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] Add Fugu-style model orchestration layer

Implements behaviour-level model fusion (no weight merging) as an
inference-time orchestrator over a heterogeneous self-hosted worker pool,
exposed through single OpenAI-compatible virtual models.

- Tier-A router (fugu-auto): rule-based task classifier (code / reasoning /
  zh / general) with capability priors, cost penalty, and confidence-based
  escalation to Tier-B or the strongest worker.
- Tier-B conductor (fugu-ultra): bounded (<=5 step) Thinker -> Worker ->
  Verifier -> Synthesizer DAG; verifier forced to a different model than the
  producer; per-step access lists gate cross-step visibility.
- Access-list data governance via X-Secret-Level (workers excluded when a
  request's sensitivity exceeds their secret_max_level).
- Worker dispatch reuses store + balancer health/capacity/load-balancing.
- Virtual models surfaced in /v1/models; full admission (rate limit / quota /
  concurrency / queue) and streaming (SSE wrap) supported.
- Prometheus metrics: orchestration routes / escalations / steps.
- Config schema + validation, sample three-model pool (gpt-oss-120b,
  gemma-4-26b, qwen3.6-27b), unit tests, README section, docs/orchestration.md
  with the learned-router/conductor training roadmap.

